TITLE: U.S. officials continue to press Russia for access to WNBA star Brittney Griner
SUMMARY: A person close to the situation confirmed to NBC News that Griner was "OK" and that her Russian legal team has met with her.

TITLE: Biden warns Xi of global backlash if China helps Russia's attack on Ukraine
SUMMARY: Biden and Chinese Pres. Xi Jinping agreed to work for peace in Ukraine. But China refused to say Russia was responsible for its brutal invasion of the country.

TITLE: Here's what Chinese state media is saying ahead of Xi's call with Biden
SUMMARY: While Chinese state media have tacked away from primarily pro-Russian coverage of the war with Ukraine, one of the consistent messages remains: Blame the U.S.

TITLE: How the Russia-Ukraine war could hit China's trade
SUMMARY: China's trade surplus could narrow to $238 billion this year – about 35% of the historic $676 billion attained last year, according to ANZ Research estimates.

TITLE: Ex-New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo considers running against Kathy Hochul despite opposition from his own party
SUMMARY: Andrew Cuomo is speaking with allies about possibly running against New York Gov. Kathy Hochul. Democratic Party officials scoff at the idea.

TITLE: Russia makes some debt payments in dollars, report says, as it seeks to avoid historic debt default
SUMMARY: The payment on the two eurobond coupons is a key test for Russia.

TITLE: Biden details new aid to Ukraine, promises "more in the days and weeks ahead" to help combat Russia invasion
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden condemned Russian leader Vladimir Putin for inflicting "appalling devastation" on Ukraine.

TITLE: Ukraine President Zelenskyy invokes Pearl Harbor, Sept. 11 in asking U.S. Congress to help fight Russia invasion
SUMMARY: Ukraine President Volodymyr Zelenskyy addressed Congress seeking more aid to fight against its invasion by Russia.

TITLE: White House says U.S. will run out of money to fight pandemic if Congress doesn't pass Covid funding bill
SUMMARY: The White House is urging Congress to pass $22.5 billion in Covid spending, warning the U.S. is running out of money to fight the virus.

TITLE: Biden signs government funding bill that includes $13.6 billion in Ukraine aid
SUMMARY: Biden signed a funding bill that will keep the government running through September and send $13.6 billion in aid to Ukraine.

TITLE: U.S. lobbyists connect Ukraine officials with powerful allies to help in war against Russia
SUMMARY: At least one U.S. company and a separate lawyer each recently disclosed to DOJ that they started working for Ukrainian officials since the Russian invasion.

TITLE: China says it wants to steer clear of U.S. sanctions over Russia's invasion of Ukraine
SUMMARY: Since Russia's attack on Ukraine, China has refused to call it an invasion and said it plans to maintain normal trade with both countries.

TITLE: Putin's invasion of Ukraine will knock 30 years of progress off the Russian economy
SUMMARY: Russia’s 40-year effort to create a Western-style market economy is one more casualty of Putin’s invasion of Ukraine.

TITLE: A guide to what Russia and Ukraine want from talks — and where the red lines are
SUMMARY: As Russian forces pummel towns, villages and cities across Ukraine, pressure is growing on officials from both side to reach a resolution.

TITLE: Leaders of NATO countries discuss plans to meet in Brussels next week, officials say
SUMMARY: The meeting would serve as a high-level show of force for NATO countries, which have forged a stronger bond in response to Russia's unprovoked attack.

TITLE: Manchin comes out against Biden Fed nominee Raskin, throwing her confirmation into doubt
SUMMARY: Sen. Joe Manchin, the most conservative Democrat in the Senate, said he is opposed to Sarah Bloom Raskin's nomination to the Federal Reserve.

TITLE: Portraits of war: See how the attack on Ukraine has affected its people
SUMMARY: Since Russia invaded Ukraine last month, more than 2.5 million people have been displaced.

TITLE: White House considers a potential Biden trip to Europe amid escalating violence in Ukraine
SUMMARY: The White House is weighing a presidential trip to Europe as Russia's invasion of Ukraine escalates.

TITLE: With Putin's war in Europe, the legacy of Germany's Merkel is now being seen in a very different light
SUMMARY: The former German leader was known for speaking Russian and keeping diplomatic ties with Putin.

TITLE: If Putin uses chemical weapons in Ukraine it's a 'game changer' for NATO
SUMMARY: Western officials and strategists say that there are good reasons to fear Moscow potentially using unconventional and outlawed weapons.

TITLE: China is seen pursuing its 'own interests' as it decides whether to help Russia
SUMMARY: All eyes have been on what the Chinese will do as Western sanctions hit Russia's economy.

TITLE: 'For the first time in history anyone can join a war': Volunteers join Russia-Ukraine cyber fight
SUMMARY: Cyber warfare is being waged, not only between Ukraine and Russia, but on behalf of these countries by “digital soldiers” around the world.

TITLE: China is 'deeply' worried about Ukraine crisis, Premier Li Keqiang says
SUMMARY: China is "deeply" worried about the "crisis" in Ukraine, Premier Li Keqiang said Friday, warning that sanctions will hurt global growth.

TITLE: VPN use in Russia is surging as citizens try to bypass government's tightening internet control
SUMMARY: Russia has blocked access to Meta-owned Facebook and restricted access to Twitter. Russians are using VPNs to try to bypass increasing internet controls.

TITLE: 'Golden passports' for the rich face new restrictions in global crackdown on Russian oligarchs
SUMMARY: Sweeping sanctions against Putin's oligarchs has led governments to limit and in some cases end their lucrative pay-for-passport programs.

TITLE: Trump loses bid to countersue rape accuser E. Jean Carroll, judge rules in scathing decision
SUMMARY: E. Jean Carroll has said Donald Trump raped her in the mid-1990s in a dressing room in a New York department store. He denies her claim.

TITLE: Relying on sanctions to stop Russia could go 'terribly wrong,' says Niall Ferguson
SUMMARY: The Russians have sustained more casualties than expected, but are still "advancing steadily," said Niall Ferguson of the Hoover Institution.

TITLE: Biden to ban U.S. imports of Russian vodka, diamonds and seafood
SUMMARY: The latest steps to punish Moscow for invading Ukraine were revealed after Biden called on the U.S. to revoke Russia's "most favored nation" trading status.

TITLE: Biden calls for an end to Russia's 'most favored nation' trade status
SUMMARY: Biden called on Congress to revoke Russia's "most favored nation" status. He also banned imports of Russian vodka and seafood and exports of U.S. luxury goods.

TITLE: Disney pauses political donations in Florida, CEO Chapek apologizes for silence over 'Don't Say Gay' bill
SUMMARY: Disney CEO Bob Chapek apologized for not being a "stronger ally" for the LGBTQ+ community and for the company's silence over Florida's "Don't Say Gay" bill.
